IPsecDescription.name: IPsecDescription
IPsecDescription.description: Optional description of a table entry.

IPsecPortNumber.name: IPsecPortNumber
IPsecPortNumber.description: A port number value. 0 is the wildcard value to match any port.

IPsecPrefixLength.name: IPsecPrefixLength
IPsecPrefixLength.description: Significant bits in an IPv6 address prefix. 0..32 is the valid range for IPv4 addresses. 0..128 is valid for IPv6 addresses

IPsecULProtocol.name: IPsecULProtocol
IPsecULProtocol.description: An upper-layer protocol number. 255 is the wildcard value to match any protocol.

IPsecOperationalState.name: IPsecOperationalState
IPsecOperationalState.description: Operational state. enabled(1) - The entry is enabled. disabled(2) - The entry is administratively disabled or DNS resolution has experienced a permanent failure. dnspending(3) - Awaiting DNS resolution before making the entry active.

alaIPsecSecurityKeyTable.name: alaIPsecSecurityKeyTable
alaIPsecSecurityKeyTable.description: Table allowing the configuration of the switch's IPsec security key. The security key is used to encrypt and IPsec related information retained in permanent storage. There is always a single row in this table with an index value of 1.

alaIPsecSecurityKeyID.name: alaIPsecSecurityKeyID
alaIPsecSecurityKeyID.description: The row's identifier. Only one entry is ever present, with an ID value of 1.

alaIPsecSecurityKeyCurrent.name: alaIPsecSecurityKeyCurrent
alaIPsecSecurityKeyCurrent.description: The current value of the 16-byte IPsec security key. If an attempt is made to read the value of this object, a zero-length octet string will be returned.

alaIPsecSecurityKeyNew.name: alaIPsecSecurityKeyNew
alaIPsecSecurityKeyNew.description: Used to set a new 16-byte value for the IPsec security key. Both alaIPsecSecurityKeyCurrent (with its correct value) and alaIPsecSecurityKeyNew must be specified in the same SNMP SET message. If alaIPsecSecurityKeyCurrent is not present, or if its value is incorrect, the attempt to set a new key will fail. If an attempt is made to read the value of this object, a zero-length octet string will be returned.

alaIPsecStatisticsTable.name: alaIPsecStatisticsTable
alaIPsecStatisticsTable.description: Table allowing the IPv6 statistics to be retrieved.

alaIPsecStatisticsProtocol.name: alaIPsecStatisticsProtocol
alaIPsecStatisticsProtocol.description: IP protocol version covered by the IPsec statistics.

alaIPsecStatisticsInSuccessful.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInSuccessful
alaIPsecStatisticsInSuccessful.description: Number of incoming packets requiring IPsec processing that were successfully handled.

alaIPsecStatisticsInPolicyViolation.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInPolicyViolation
alaIPsecStatisticsInPolicyViolation.description: Number of incoming packets that were dropped because of policy violations.

alaIPsecStatisticsInNoSA.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInNoSA
alaIPsecStatisticsInNoSA.description: Number of incoming packets dropped because no matching SA was found.

alaIPsecStatisticsInUnknownSPI.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInUnknownSPI
alaIPsecStatisticsInUnknownSPI.description: Number of incoming packets dropped because the SPI was unknown.

alaIPsecStatisticsInAHReplay.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInAHReplay
alaIPsecStatisticsInAHReplay.description: Number of incoming packets that failed the AH replay check.

alaIPsecStatisticsInESPReplay.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInESPReplay
alaIPsecStatisticsInESPReplay.description: Number of incoming packets taht failed the ESP replay check.

alaIPsecStatisticsInAHAuthenticationSucc.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInAHAuthenticationSuccess
alaIPsecStatisticsInAHAuthenticationSucc.description: Number of incoming packets that successfully passed AH authentication.

alaIPsecStatisticsInAHAuthenticationFail.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInAHAuthenticationFail
alaIPsecStatisticsInAHAuthenticationFail.description: Number of incoming packets that failed AH authentication.

alaIPsecStatisticsInESPAuthenticationSuc.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInESPAuthenticationSuccess
alaIPsecStatisticsInESPAuthenticationSuc.description: Number of incoming packets that successfully passed ESP authentication.

alaIPsecStatisticsInESPAuthenticationFai.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInESPAuthenticationFail
alaIPsecStatisticsInESPAuthenticationFai.description: Number of incoming packets that failed ESP authentication.

alaIPsecStatisticsInBadPacket.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInBadPacket
alaIPsecStatisticsInBadPacket.description: Number of incoming packets requiring IPsec processing that were not valid.

alaIPsecStatisticsInNoMemory.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInNoMemory
alaIPsecStatisticsInNoMemory.description: Number of incoming IPsec packets dropped because no memory was available.

alaIPsecStatisticsOutSuccessful.name: alaIPsecStatisticsOutSuccessful
alaIPsecStatisticsOutSuccessful.description: Number of outgoing packets requiring IPsec processing that were successfully handled.

alaIPsecStatisticsOutPolicyViolation.name: alaIPsecStatisticsOutPolicyViolation
alaIPsecStatisticsOutPolicyViolation.description: Number of outgoing packets dropped because of a policy violation.

alaIPsecStatisticsOutNoSA.name: alaIPsecStatisticsOutNoSA
alaIPsecStatisticsOutNoSA.description: Number of outgoing packets dropped because no matching SA was found.

alaIPsecStatisticsOutBadPacket.name: alaIPsecStatisticsOutBadPacket
alaIPsecStatisticsOutBadPacket.description: Number of outgoing packets requiring IPsec processing that were not valid.

alaIPsecStatisticsOutNoMemory.name: alaIPsecStatisticsOutNoMemory
alaIPsecStatisticsOutNoMemory.description: Number of outgoing IPsec packets dropped because no memory was available.

alaIPsecStatisticsInDiscarded.name: alaIPsecStatisticsInDiscarded
alaIPsecStatisticsInDiscarded.description: Number of incoming packets dropped because they matched a discard policy.

alaIPsecStatisticsOutDiscarded.name: alaIPsecStatisticsOutDiscarded
alaIPsecStatisticsOutDiscarded.description: Number of outgoing packets dropped because they matched a discard policy.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyTable.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyTable
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyTable.description: Table allowing the configuration of IPsec security policies.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyID.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyID
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyID.description: A unique identifier for this security policy. When creating a new policy, a zero value must be specified. An available policy ID will then be automatically assigned to the policy.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicySourceType.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicySourceType
alaIPsecSecurityPolicySourceType.description: The type of source address specified. Currently only ipv6(2) is allowed.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicySource.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicySource
alaIPsecSecurityPolicySource.description: The source of packets covered by this policy.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicySourcePrefixLength.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicySourcePrefixLength
alaIPsecSecurityPolicySourcePrefixLength.description: The number of bits of the source address used to determine which packets are covered by this policy. The default value varies depending upon the type of source address specified: IPv4 - 32 IPv6 - 128 DNS name - 0 (any other value is ignored)

alaIPsecSecurityPolicySourcePort.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicySourcePort
alaIPsecSecurityPolicySourcePort.description: The source port of packets covered by this policy. To match packets from any port, specify the 0 wildcard value. A wildcard policy will only be used when there is no exact match to a destination port in another entry.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestinationType.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestinationType
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestinationType.description: The type of destination address specified. Currently only ipv6(2) is allowed.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestination.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestination
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestination.description: The destination of packets covered by this policy.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestinationPrefixL.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestinationPrefixLength
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestinationPrefixL.description: The number of bits of the destination prefix used to determine which packets are covered by this policy. The default value varies depending upon the type of destination address specified: IPv4 - 32 IPv6 - 128 DNS name - 0 (any other value is ignored)

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestinationPort.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestinationPort
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDestinationPort.description: The destination port of packets covered by this policy. To match packets from any port, specify the 0 wildcard value. A wildcard policy will only be used when there is no exact match to a destination port in another entry.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyULProtocol.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyULProtocol
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyULProtocol.description: The upper-layer protocol of packets covered by this policy. To match all protocols, specify the 255 wildcard value. A wildcard policy will only be used when there is no exact match to the protocol value specified in another entry.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyICMPv6Type.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyICMPv6Type
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyICMPv6Type.description: If the upper-layer protocol is ICMPv6, an ICMPv6 type value may be specified to restrict the policy to a specific packet type. To match all ICMPv6 packets, the 0 wildcard value should be specified.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDirection.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDirection
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDirection.description: The direction of traffic covered by this policy.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDescription.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDescription
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyDescription.description: A detailed description of this policy.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyAction.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyAction
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyAction.description: The action to take on traffic covered by this policy. discard(0) means that all traffic covered by the policy will be discarded. none(1) means that no IPsec processing will be done on the traffic covered by this policy. ipsec(2) means that IPsec processing will take place on the traffic. One or more rules should be defined in the IPsec Rule Table. If no rules are defined processing is identical to none(0) being specified.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyAdminState.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyAdminState
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyAdminState.description: Allows a policy to be administratively enabled or disabled.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyOperationalState.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyOperationalState
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyOperationalState.description: The operational state of this policy.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyPriority.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyPriority
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyPriority.description: The priority for this policy. When traffic would be covered by multiple policies the policy with the highest priority value is used. If two policies have the same priority, the one configured first has precedence.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRowStatus.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRowStatus
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of security policy entries.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleTable.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleTable
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleTable.description: Table allowing the configuration of the IPsec rules for a security policy.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleIndex.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleIndex
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleIndex.description: Index specifying the order in which multiple rules for the same security policy will be applied. Rules are indexed by the order in which they are applied to the original payload. For example, for a security policy where an IPv6 payload should be protected by an ESP header, which should be protected by an AH header, there would be two Rule Table entries. The ESP entry would have an index of 1 (first rule applied to the payload). The AH entry would have an index of 2 (second rule applied).

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleProtocol.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleProtocol
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleProtocol.description: Indicates the type of header required by the rule.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleMode.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleMode
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleMode.description: The mode in which the rule's protocol is running. At present, only transport(1) is allowed. Until tunnel mode is supported, transport(1) will be treated as the default value.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleRowStatus.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleRowStatus
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyRuleRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of security policy IPsec rule entries.

alaIPsecSAConfigTable.name: alaIPsecSAConfigTable
alaIPsecSAConfigTable.description: Table allowing the manual configuration of Security Associations in the Security Association Database (SAD).

alaIPsecSAConfigID.name: alaIPsecSAConfigID
alaIPsecSAConfigID.description: A unique identifier for this manually configured SA. When creating a new SA, a zero value must be specified. An available ID will then be automatically assigned to the SA.

alaIPsecSAConfigType.name: alaIPsecSAConfigType
alaIPsecSAConfigType.description: The type of this SA: AH or ESP. Once set, the type may not be changed.

alaIPsecSAConfigSourceType.name: alaIPsecSAConfigSourceType
alaIPsecSAConfigSourceType.description: The type of source address specified. Currently only ipv6(2) is allowed.

alaIPsecSAConfigSource.name: alaIPsecSAConfigSource
alaIPsecSAConfigSource.description: The source of packets covered by this SA.

alaIPsecSAConfigDestinationType.name: alaIPsecSAConfigDestinationType
alaIPsecSAConfigDestinationType.description: The type of destination address specified. Currently only ipv6(2) is allowed.

alaIPsecSAConfigDestination.name: alaIPsecSAConfigDestination
alaIPsecSAConfigDestination.description: The destination of packets covered by this SA.

alaIPsecSAConfigSPI.name: alaIPsecSAConfigSPI
alaIPsecSAConfigSPI.description: The Security Parameters Index (SPI) of this SA.

alaIPsecSAConfigName.name: alaIPsecSAConfigName
alaIPsecSAConfigName.description: The name of this manually configured SA.

alaIPsecSAConfigDescription.name: alaIPsecSAConfigDescription
alaIPsecSAConfigDescription.description: A detailed description for the manually created IPsec SA.

alaIPsecSAConfigEncryptionAlgorithm.name: alaIPsecSAConfigEncryptionAlgorithm
alaIPsecSAConfigEncryptionAlgorithm.description: For an ESP SA, defines the encryption algorithm to be used. null(11) should be specified if ESP is being used for integrity only. If null(11) is specified, alaIPsecSAConfigAuthenticationAlgorithm may not be none(0). aesctr(13) is not valid for manually configured SAs. The value of this object is none(0) for AH SAs.

alaIPsecSAConfigEncryptionKeyLength.name: alaIPsecSAConfigEncryptionKeyLength
alaIPsecSAConfigEncryptionKeyLength.description: For those algorithms where multiple key lengths are supported, specifies the key length to be used. Zero may be specified to use the default key length.

alaIPsecSAConfigAuthenticationAlgorithm.name: alaIPsecSAConfigAuthenticationAlgorithm
alaIPsecSAConfigAuthenticationAlgorithm.description: Defines the authentication algorithm to be used. For ESP SAs, none(0) may be specified for encryption-only ESP. For ESP integrity-only, ESP integrity and encryption, or for AH SAs, hmacmd5(2), hmacsha1(3), or aesxcbcmac(9) must be specified.

alaIPsecSAConfigAdminState.name: alaIPsecSAConfigAdminState
alaIPsecSAConfigAdminState.description: Allows a manually configured SA to be administratively enabled or disabled.

alaIPsecSAConfigOperationalState.name: alaIPsecSAConfigOperationalState
alaIPsecSAConfigOperationalState.description: The operational state of the manually configured SA.

alaIPsecSAConfigRowStatus.name: alaIPsecSAConfigRowStatus
alaIPsecSAConfigRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of manually configured IPsec SAs.

alaIPsecKeyTable.name: alaIPsecKeyTable
alaIPsecKeyTable.description: Table used to configure the keys used by manually configured Security Associations in the IPsec Security Association Configuration table.

alaIPsecKeyEntry.name: alaIPsecKeyEntry
alaIPsecKeyEntry.description: An IPsec key. Keys in the table must be uniquely identified by the combination of key type and key name. However, since the key name can be up to 255 characters, beyond the 128-element size limit for SNMP index objects, the key ID is used to uniquely identify a key for SNMP access.

alaIPsecKeyID.name: alaIPsecKeyID
alaIPsecKeyID.description: A unique identifier for this key. When creating a new key, a zero value must be specified. An available ID will then be automatically assigned to the key.

alaIPsecKeyType.name: alaIPsecKeyType
alaIPsecKeyType.description: Indicates if the key is to be used for encryption or authentication by a SA. Once a key is created, its type may not be changed.

alaIPsecKeyName.name: alaIPsecKeyName
alaIPsecKeyName.description: The name of the key. For manually-configured SA keys, the name is limited to a maximum length of 20 characters and should correspond to an entry in the alaIPsecSAConfigTable. The key name may not be changed once a key is created.

alaIPsecKey.name: alaIPsecKey
alaIPsecKey.description: The key value. The value specified must match the required key length for the algorithm using the key. If an attempt is made to read the value of this object a zero-length octet string will be returned.

alaIPsecKeyEncrypted.name: alaIPsecKeyEncrypted
alaIPsecKeyEncrypted.description: If true, the key value is specified in AOS encrypted form. For example, keys being restored from the configuration file.

alaIPsecKeyRowStatus.name: alaIPsecKeyRowStatus
alaIPsecKeyRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and removal of keys.

alaIPsecErrorsTable.name: alaIPsecErrorsTable
alaIPsecErrorsTable.description: Table allowing retrieval of the IPsec error counters.

alaIPsecErrorsProtocol.name: alaIPsecErrorsProtocol
alaIPsecErrorsProtocol.description: IP protocol version covered by the IPsec error counters.

alaIPsecErrorsInPolicyViolation.name: alaIPsecErrorsInPolicyViolation
alaIPsecErrorsInPolicyViolation.description: Number of incoming packets that were dropped because of policy violations.

alaIPsecErrorsInNoSA.name: alaIPsecErrorsInNoSA
alaIPsecErrorsInNoSA.description: Number of incoming packets dropped because no matching SA was found.

alaIPsecErrorsInReplay.name: alaIPsecErrorsInReplay
alaIPsecErrorsInReplay.description: Number of incoming packets that failed a replay check.

alaIPsecErrorsInAuthenticationFail.name: alaIPsecErrorsInAuthenticationFail
alaIPsecErrorsInAuthenticationFail.description: Number of incoming packets that failed authentication.

alaIPsecErrorsInDiscarded.name: alaIPsecErrorsInDiscarded
alaIPsecErrorsInDiscarded.description: Number of incoming packets dropped because they matched a discard policy.

alaIPsecErrorsInOther.name: alaIPsecErrorsInOther
alaIPsecErrorsInOther.description: Number of incoming packets dropped for a reason not otherwise counted.

alaIPsecErrorsOutNoSA.name: alaIPsecErrorsOutNoSA
alaIPsecErrorsOutNoSA.description: Number of outgoing packets dropped because no matching SA was found.

alaIPsecErrorsOutDiscarded.name: alaIPsecErrorsOutDiscarded
alaIPsecErrorsOutDiscarded.description: Number of outgoing packets dropped because they matched a discard policy.

alaIPsecErrorsOutOther.name: alaIPsecErrorsOutOther
alaIPsecErrorsOutOther.description: Number of outgoing packets dropped for a reason not otherwise counted.

alaIPsecCompliance.name: alaIPsecCompliance
alaIPsecCompliance.description: The compliance statement for Alcatel switches implementing ALCATEL-IND1-IPSEC-MIB.

alaIPsecConfigGroup.name: alaIPsecConfigGroup
alaIPsecConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects to support global configuration of IPsec.

alaIPsecSecurityPolicyGroup.name: alaIPsecSecurityPolicyGroup
alaIPsecSecurityPolicyGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of IPsec security policies.

alaIPsecSAConfigGroup.name: alaIPsecSAConfigGroup
alaIPsecSAConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of manually configured IPsec SAs.

alaIPsecKeyGroup.name: alaIPsecKeyGroup
alaIPsecKeyGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of keys.

alaIPsecCountersGroup.name: alaIPsecCountersGroup
alaIPsecCountersGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of IPsec counters.

alaIPsecStatisticsGroup.name: alaIPsecStatisticsGroup
alaIPsecStatisticsGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of IPsec statistics.
